txt.en: 'You urge us to leave, stranger? We are safer here than we would be on the frozen fields, where we have seen Orcs riding on Wargs. Some have even dared approach us, but our arrows sent them off again.\n\n'No, we could not hope to leave while such deadly foes roam unchallenged through the lands.'
'I am glad you spilled the blood of the Warg-riders, friend. I am not sure that we will leave, but I am glad we will be safer whether we stay or go.'
The fishermen complain of Warg-riding Orcs harrying them more and more frequently, making them uneasy.
The fishermen are at their small encampment on the banks of the Isingmere in the northern Whitshaws.\n\nYou should speak with the fishermen.
Harrying Orcs riding on Wargs can be found in the northern Whitshaws.\n\nYou should defeat several Orkish Warg-riders near the fishermen's haunt.
